description:
Stages in Quest each have three of the following 
four difficulties: 
- {color: #3366FF}NORMAL{color} 
- {color: #FF9900}HARD{color} 
- {color: #FF0000}Z-HARD{color} 
- {color: #9966FF}SUPER{color}

You can quit during a Quest (including map and battle) by going 
to "MENU" on the bottom right side of your screen and selecting 
{color: #FFFF00}"Abandon Quest."{color}

Each character has a Type. Below is the type compatibility chart:

·{color: #FF3333}STR (Red){color}: Strong against{color: #FFCC00} PHY (Orange){color}, 
  weak against {color: #66CCCC}AGL (Blue){color}
·{color: #66CCCC}AGL (Blue){color}: Strong against{color: #FF3333} STR (Red){color}, 
  weak against {color: #00CC00}TEQ (Green){color}
·{color: #00CC00}TEQ (Green){color}: Strong against{color: #66CCCC} AGL (Blue){color}, 
  weak against {color: #CC66FF}INT (Purple){color}
·{color: #CC66FF}INT (Purple){color}: Strong against{color: #00CC00} TEQ (Green){color}, 
  weak against {color: #FFCC00}PHY (Orange){color}
·{color: #FFCC00}PHY (Orange){color}: Strong against{color: #CC66FF} INT (Purple){color}, 
  weak against {color: #FF3333}STR (Red){color}

When you're up against a weaker Type, you'll do more damage, 
but when you're up against a stronger Type, the enemy will 
guard against your attack and you'll do less damage.

When the enemy is the first to attack, they will attack the 
character on the far left. In all other cases, enemies will target 
the {color: #FFFF00}"character who attacked just before them."{color}

{center: begin}Daily Missions{center} 
{center: begin}Normal Missions{center} 
{center: begin}Event Missions{center} 
{center: begin}Trial Missions{center} 
{center: begin}Portal of Memories{center} 

Missions are divided into the 5 types shown above. 

"Event Missions" also include time-limited missions related 
to events. You can claim the rewards of completed missions at 
any time, except for Daily Missions. Please note you will not 
be able to claim the Daily Mission rewards if you do not 
claim them before the daily update of the missions.

If a mission is completed, it will be marked with {color: #FFFF00}"CLEARED!"{color} 
on the mission list, and its frame will become yellow. 
You can tap on it to claim the rewards.

{color : #FFFF00}Baba's Shop{color} is a place where you can acquire various items by 
using your Trade Points, Zeni and Treasure.  

{size:25}{color : #FFFF00}▼Trade Points{color}{size}

{color : #FFFF00}Slightly raises the power of a Super Attack.{color} 
Any additional effects of the Super Attack will not change. 
The effect increases along with the skill level.

{size : 26}7. Recovery Boost{size}

{size : 24}{color : #FFFF00}{outline : #FF0000, 2}Button for Random Training Partners{outline}{color}{size}
Tapping the Random button for training partners automatically 
sets up to 5 characters with a rarity of N or R.

{size : 24}{color : #FFFF00}{outline : #FF0000, 2}Switch Button{outline}{color}{size}
Tap the Switch button to toggle between "Until Next Level" and 
"Until Max Level".

{size : 24}{color : #FFFF00}{outline : #FF0000, 2}Same Type Bonus{outline}{color}{size} 

Using Training Partners or Training Items of the same Type 
as the Training Character will grant an extra 50% EXP.

{size : 24}{color : #FFFF00}{outline : #FF0000, 2}= About Keys ={outline}{color}{size}
Keys are required to challenge events 
from the Portal of Memories.

{size : 24}{color : #FFFF00}{outline : #FF0000, 2}- Using Keys{outline}{color}{size}
The type and number of Keys required will vary
depending on the event.

{size : 24}{color : #FFFF00}{outline : #FF0000, 2}= Trial Missions ={outline}{color}{size} 
You can take on high difficulty Trial Missions 
in each stage. Complete Trial Missions to get 
items including special Treasures as rewards. 

{size: 24}{outline: #FF0000, 2}{color: #FFFF00}- How to Play{outline}{color}{size} 
{color: #FFFF00}Step 1: Check Available Trial Missions!{color} 
Check the information of Trial Missions and 
rewards of each stage.

{color: #FFFF00}Step 2: Take on a Trial Mission!{color} 
After checking the Trial Mission and rewards, 
proceed to the stage.

{color: #FFFF00}Step 3: Choose Difficulty!{color}
The difficulties where you can take on "Trial Missions" 
will be marked with a scroll icon.

{size: 24}{outline: #FF0000, 2}{color: #FFFF00}= What Are Active Skills? ={outline}{color}{size} 
These are special skills that belong only to certain characters.
They can be activated in battle when certain conditions are met.

These Skill Orbs will be automatically removed and returned 
to the "Items" page when being replaced by another Skill Orb. 
{color : #FFFF00}* Please note that you cannot remove them directly.{color}

{size: 24}{outline: #FF0000, 2}{color: #FFFF00}= What Are Conditional Super Attacks? ={outline}{color}{size} 
These are special Super Attacks only certain characters have. 
They will be activated in battle when certain conditions are met.

{size: 24}{outline: #FF0000, 2}{color: #FFFF00}What Is a Visual Change?{outline}{color}{size} 
This is a special trick that belongs only to certain characters. The characters will undergo a change in appearance when 
certain conditions are met in battle.

Clearing maps will allow you to use auto mode for 
maps and battles (this does not apply to Quests). 
{color : #FFFF00}* There are certain maps on which auto mode cannot be used.{color}

{color : #FFFF00}* Any incomplete purchases will be canceled.{color} 
{color : #FFFF00}* Dragon Stones cannot be transferred 
between different operating systems.{color} 
{color : #FFFF00}* Please note that your "Daily Capsule" subscription 
cannot be transferred between different operating systems.{color} 
* Only the latest Transfer Code can be used. 
* The Transfer Code will become invalid once 
the device transfer is complete.
